{"claim_id": "claim_018", "text": "For LC-MS/MS data, data dependent acquisition (DDA) is the most used approach for generating fragmentation spectra.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "the\nmost used is data dependent acquisition (DDA) also known as the top-n method.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_xcms/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [31622, 31703], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["spectra_package"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_019", "text": "In DDA, the top N most intense ions are selected for fragmentation before the cycle starts again.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "In\nthis method the top N most intense ions (m/z values) from a MS1 scan are\nselected for fragmentation in the next N scans before the cycle starts\nagain.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_xcms/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [31704, 31857], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": []}
{"claim_id": "claim_021", "text": "The example DDA and SWATH data files are from reversed-phase LC-MS/MS runs of the Agilent Pesticide mix.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "The data files used are reversed-phase LC-MS/MS runs from\nthe Agilent Pesticide mix obtained from a Sciex 6600 Triple ToF operated in\nSWATH acquisition mode.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_xcms/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [33139, 33296], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "data", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000006", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["swath_acquisition_mode"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_022", "text": "Most signal in the DDA dataset was measured between approximately 200 and 600 seconds.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "most of the signal is measured between ~ 200 and 600\nseconds", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_xcms/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [33885, 33945], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "data", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000006", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": []}
{"claim_id": "claim_023", "text": "In the DDA dataset, chromatographic peak detection identified peaks at specific m/z values.", "claim_type": "implicit", "source_excerpt": "In total", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_xcms/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [9969, 9978], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "inference", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": []}
{"claim_id": "claim_026", "text": "CentWaveParam was used for chromatographic peak detection with snthresh of 5, noise of 100, ppm of 10, and peakwidth of 3 to 30.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "cwp <- CentWaveParam(snthresh = 5, noise = 100, ppm = 10,\n                     peakwidth = c(3, 30))", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_xcms/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [36564, 36664], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "data", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000006", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["centwave_param"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_027", "text": "The chromPeakSpectra method extracts MS2 spectra with precursor m/z and retention time within the range of chromatographic peaks.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "MS2 spectra with their precursor\nm/z and retention time within the rt and m/z range of the chromatographic peak\nare returned.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_xcms/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [37258, 37383], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["spectra_package", "chrom_peak_spectra_method"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_028", "text": "The returned Spectra from chromPeakSpectra contains a chrom_peak_id spectra variable that identifies the associated chromatographic peak.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "The returned `Spectra` contains also the reference to the respective\nchromatographic peak as additional *spectra variable* `\"chrom_peak_id\"` that contains\nthe identifier for the chromatographic peak", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_xcms/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [37934, 38132], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["spectra_package", "chrom_peak_spectra_method"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_029", "text": "An example chromatographic peak of an ion with m/z 304.1131 was identified in the DDA dataset.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "As an example we use a chromatographic peak of an ion with an m/z of\n304.1131", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_xcms/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [38920, 38997], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "data", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000006", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": []}
